I just saw this as well, but with a different crate:


{code:java}
        Checking arrow v2.0.0-SNAPSHOT (/Users/runner/work/arrow/arrow/rust/arrow)

    
   error[E0463]: can't find crate for `serde_derive`
   
      --> arrow/src/datatypes.rs:36:5
    
       |
    
    36 | use serde_derive::{Deserialize, Serialize};
    
       |     ^^^^^^^^^^^^ can't find crate {code}
 

failed build: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/7892/checks?check_run_id=943030043

A workaround to force the checks to rerun, as explained in https://stackoverflow.com/questions/52408592/how-to-relaunch-github-check-without-pushing-new-commits is to push an empty commit:

{code}
git commit -m 'retrigger checks' --allow-empty
git push
{code}
